<HEAD>Pope Baptizes 44 Babies</HEAD>
<DATELINE>VATICAN CITY (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Pope John Paul II baptized 44 babies from
five countries Sunday in a new year's tradition he began in 1980.
   During the ceremony in the Hall of the Benedictions of the
Apostolic Palace, the pope christened 36 babies from Italy, five
from his native Poland and one each from Argentina, Nigeria and
India.
   Later, in his noon address from a window overlooking St. Peter's
Square, he urged the faithful to recognize ``the commitments assumed
for us by our parents, godmothers and godfathers.''
   John Paul has baptized nearly 300 babies in the past nine years.
