<HEAD>Truck Falls Into Ravine Killing 13</HEAD>
<DATELINE>JAKARTA, Indonesia (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A truck plunged into a ravine in north
Sumatra, killing 13 people and seriously injuring 10, a newspaper
reported Sunday.
   The driver lost control of the truck on a curve, and it fell into
a 45-foot-deep ravine, the Kompas newspaper reported.
   It was not clear why the truck, which was hauling sap, was
carrying 23 people in addition to the driver. The accident occurred
Thursday about 275 miles south of Medan, a provincial capital.
   The newspaper quoted unidentified victims as saying the driver
was only slightly injured in the accident and promptly fled the
scene.
