<HEAD>Reward Offered In Fatal Subway Stabbing</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LONDON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The London Underground offered an $18,000 reward
Sunday for information leading to the arrest of two young men
involved in the fatal stabbing of a Turkish student in a subway
station.
   Hakan Koseoglu, 17, of Denizli, Turkey, died instantly from a
single stab wound to the heart in the Holborn subway station on Dec.
9 as he tried to fight off two muggers who had grabbed a gold chain
from his neck.
   His cousin, with whom the dead youth had been staying, and two
members of the public who saw the attack grabbed the assailants but
were unable to hold them. Police believe they escaped on a train.
