<FIRST>u i AM-Khomeini-Gorbachev     01-08 0321</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Khomeini-Gorbachev,0331</SECOND>
<HEAD>Khomeini Wants Gorbachev To Study Islam</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NICOSIA, Cyprus (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Ayatollah Ruhollah Khomeini has urged
Soviet President Mikhail S. Gorbachev to ask Iran for a new ideology
that would replace communism, the Islamic Republic News Agency said
Sunday.
   The agency, monitored in Nicosia, was reporting the full text of
a message sent by the ageing revolutionary patriarch to Gorbachev
last week.
   ``I expressly declare that the Islamic Republic of Iran, as the
greatest and most powerful base in the world of Islam, can easily
fill the ideological vacuum of your regime,'' the agency quoted the
message as saying.
   Khomeini's special envoy, Ayatollah Javadi Amoli, traveled to
Moscow on Friday at the head of a mission to deliver the message to
Gorbachev.
   The Iranian patriarch praised Gorbachev for his decision to allow
more religious freedom in the Soviet Union, saying this proved he
had turned his back on communism, ``a bankrupt ideology,'' the
agency said.
   But he warned the Soviet leader to avoid ``the green garden'' of
western capitalism.
   ``While there is no such thing as communism in the world anymore,
you must not get caught in the Western (capitalist) snare of the
Great Satan,'' the agency said. Iranians often refer to the United
States as the ``Great Satan.''
   ``If you look to western capitalism to solve your problems, you
will not only fail to solve the ills of your society, but leaders
who come after you will have to work to mend your mistakes,'' the
message said.
   Khomeini invited Gorbachev to send some of his ``sharp-minded
experts'' to Qom, the traditional bastion of Shiite Islam, to study
the works of Moslem ideologues and bring the message of Islam back
to the Soviet leader, the agency said.
   ``The root of the Soviet problem is not the lack of freedoms, or
the communist economy, but its long, insolent campaign against
belief in God,'' the agency quoted his message as saying.
</TEXT>
