<HEAD>Four Children Die in Mobile Home Fire</HEAD>
<HEAD>Eds: LEADS with 4 grafs to FIX typo in lead, and to CORRECT IDs of
victims, reflecting official change, in grafs 2 and 4. Picks up 5th graf,
`The mother ...'.</HEAD>
<DATELINE>LEXINGTON PARK, Md. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   An early morning fire that gutted a
mobile home killed four young brothers and sisters Sunday,
authorities said.
   The fire at a trailer park in St. Mary's County in southern
Maryland killed 2-year-old twins, Michael Dwayne Bucks and Michelle
Denise Bucks, as well as a 7-month-old sister, Latashia S. Bucks,
and a 4-year-old brother, Daniel William Bucks, said Bob Thomas, a
deputy state fire marshal.
   Three adults, including the children's mother, escaped, he said.
The cause of the fire was not immediately determined.
   Thomas said the twins and Daniel were in a bedroom in the center
of the mobile home, while the infant was in her mother's bedroom at
the back of the mobile home.
   The mother, Mary Young, 20; her boyfriend, Mitchell Dove, 25; and
Ms. Young's sister Alice Young, whose age wasn't immediately
available, told authorities they tried to rescue the children but
were driven back by the fire.
   Damage to the uninsured mobile home was estimated at $25,000,
Thomas said. It was not equipped with a smoke detector.
