   Caro Quintero is also charged with masterminding the Feb. 7,
1985, torture and slaying of U.S. Drug Enforcement Agent Enrique
Camarena. His body was found with that of his pilot at a ranch
outside Guadalajara on March 5, 1985.
   According to the newspaper, the state Supreme Justice Tribunal
``will shortly render a verdict'' on the murder charges.
   The suspects remain in prison awaiting the verdict, the Excelsior
report said.
   The bodies of the two victims were recovered near Guadalajara in
June 1985.
