<HEAD>Devotees Join To Celebrate Elvis Birthday</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MEMPHIS, Tenn. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Elvis Presley devotees took part Sunday in
a cake cutting ceremony, a breakfast and a party to celebrate the
54th anniversary of the birth of the king of rock 'n' roll.
   An estimated 2,500 people visited Presley's Graceland mansion,
compared with about 1,200 last year on his birthday, Graceland
spokeswoman Meredith Phillips said.
   Fans flock to the mansion each year during his birthday and the
anniversary of his death on Aug. 16, 1977. Presley was born in
Tupelo, Miss., on Jan. 8, 1935.
   Those who turned out early Sunday heard officials on the steps of
Graceland proclaim Elvis Presley Day in Memphis. Then fans rode
shuttle buses to the Heartbreak Hotel Restaurant for a country-style
buffet complete with Elvis' favorite extra-crispy bacon.
   Around noon a party sponsored by the Then, Now, &amp; Forever Elvis
Presley Fan Club of Memphis began at a pizza restaurant. It included
Elvis movies and concert videos and a birthday cake featuring a
likeness of Presley.
   The festivities were to be capped by two showings of ``Elvis: A
Musical Celebration'' at the historic Orpheum Theater. Fans who
bought a Graceland birthday package of admission tickets were
invited to a semi-formal cocktail party before the production's
evening showing and a chance to mingle with the cast at a
post-performance party.
