<SECOND>AM-BRF--Apartment Fire,0113</SECOND>
<HEAD>Fire At SF Apartment Building, 3 Other Structures Brought Under Control</HEAD>
<DATELINE>SAN FRANCISCO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   Firefighters rescued a woman trapped in a
blaze Sunday with a 50-foot extension ladder and directed the
evacuation of residents from 32 units. No injuries were reported.
   The blaze burned in four buildings in a residential neighborhood,
causing more than $800,000 damage, Fire Chief Fred Postel said. The
cause was not determined, but officials believed it started on the
ground floor of a four-story apartment building. The woman rescued
by firefighters was on the fourth floor.
   Nine people were displaced by the fire, according to the Red
Cross, which offered them temporary shelter.
