<FIRST>r a AM-Most-WantedFugitive     01-08 0162</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Most-Wanted Fugitive,0165</SECOND>
<HEAD>Former Miami Policeman Joins FBI Most-Wanted List</HEAD>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A former Miami police officer sought on racketeering
and narcotics charges was put on the FBI's list of the 10
most-wanted fugitives Sunday.
   Armando Garcia is wanted on charges of attempted murder of
government witnesses and drug theft, the FBI said.
   Garcia is accused of being part of a gang of officers who stole
and sold drugs and participated in 1985 in a drug raid in which
three men fleeing threats drowned in the Miami River. Ten former
Miami police officers involved in the so-called River Cops case have
pleaded guilty in federal court, and two others were tried and
convicted, the FBI said.
   The agency said the only remaining fugitives in the case are
Garcia, 26; his father, Toribio Dagobeerto Garcia, 50; and former
Miami police officer Victor Zapata, 30.
   Garcia is 5-foot-9 and 180 pounds with brown hair and a burn scar
on his left cheek.
