<FIRST>d f AM-Egypt-OPEC     01-08 0120</FIRST>
<SECOND>AM-Egypt-OPEC,0128</SECOND>
<HEAD>OPEC Secretary General Arrives For Official Visit</HEAD>
<HEAD>Subroto one word is cq</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CAIRO, Egypt (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   OPEC Secretary General Subroto arrived in
Egypt on Sunday to discuss cooperation between the cartel and
non-members on controlling oil production, the Middle East New
Agency said.
   The agency said Subroto, a former Indonesian oil minister, will
hold talks with Egyptian Oil Minister Abdel-Hady Kandil and Prime
Minister Atef Sedki on the current state of the world oil market.
   Oil prices have been on the rise since the Organization of
Petroleum Exporting Countries agreed in November to cut daily oil
production to 18.5 million barrels.
   Although Egypt is not an OPEC member, it often follows the
policies of the 13-nation cartel.
